description.narrative: Syria's conflict-affected population have their critical NFI needs met, in line with the HRP and as part of the UNICEF JOP, which contributes to Cross-Sectoral Monitoring, Data And Situation Analyses, Operations Support To Programme Delivery, Other Cross-Sectoral Programme Areas, Prevention Of Stunting And Other Forms Of Malnutrition, Treatment Of Severe Acute Malnutrition. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: MENARO delivers timely, equitable and principled humanitarian action as a complement to country office-led operations where required, including through the cross-border component of the Syria programmes as part of the Whole of Syria response.
